      "post_content": "Actually I can imagine several uses for this card, the first one is if you put anything into play with death touch, or a on damage ability like lightning reaver or lifelink. A nice combo might be play this card early on, later play where ancients tread, and have some vengeful rebirth in your deck, thereby making everything you play have burn damage on the side. Have low cost creatures like thoctars (or in worldwake maybe leatherback baloth). Play a thoctar, add 3 mana to do 5, and then another 5 for where ancients tread, and then attack for 5 next turn, and if it dies and you use vengeful rebirth on it.. same thing, it comes back into play and vengeful rebirth does at least the converted mana cost, and electropotence does another five. That is strictly a pretty great combo as far as burn is concerned. It also doesn't have to die it simply has to \"leave play,\" so you could use things like spitebellows and reveillark to either do 6 to two creatures/players or bring back 2 creatures ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Donovan_Fabian",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost26340\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_post\">Actually I can imagine several uses for this card, the first one is if you put anything into play with death touch, or a on damage ability like lightning reaver or lifelink.  A nice combo might be play this card early on, later play where ancients tread, and have some vengeful rebirth in your deck, thereby making everything you play have burn damage on the side.  Have low cost creatures like thoctars (or in worldwake maybe leatherback baloth).  Play a thoctar, add 3 mana to do 5, and then another 5 for where ancients tread, and then attack for 5 next turn, and if it dies and you use vengeful rebirth on it.. same thing, it comes back into play and vengeful rebirth does at least the converted mana cost, and electropotence does another five.  That is strictly a pretty great combo as far as burn is concerned.  It also doesn't have to die it simply has to \"leave play,\" so you could use things like spitebellows and reveillark to either do 6 to two creatures/players or bring back 2 creatures ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 26340)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '26340'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n               